title: California Pop Artist Destiny Releases New Music Video "I Feel Alive"
text:
"I Feel Alive" by Destiny , Distributed by Coast 2 Coast Video Distributions. Destiny is currently seeking blog placements, interviews, and other press opportunities.
Malibu, CA (PRWEB) October 20, 2015
Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes presents the release of the "I Feel Alive" Music Video by Destiny. This new video is currently available to view on the Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes website, with over 40k views to date.
Destiny is a 19-year-old singer/songwriter/musician from Malibu, California.
Destiny was 5 when she first appeared on the television network Univision, as part of an original tribute song for 911 victims. Before turning 12, Destiny had written and distributed 5 songs on iTunes and 23 radio stations. Destiny entered and won multiple songwriting contests. She was encouraged after reading feedback on a contest evaluation, which read: "You are already a star in my eyes." The grand prize was to see and meet the staff at Remote Control Studios, home of 4-time Grammy Award winner Hans Zimmer!" There was no turning back for Destiny.
Before her high school graduation, Destiny signed a songwriter contract with Burnett Music Group, headed by a classmate named James, son of industry leader, Mark Burnett.
Since being signed, Destiny has released two music videos, written over 125 songs in multiple genres, and had one of her original songs premiere on the TLC Series, "Answered Prayers", hosted by award winning actress and producer, Roma Downey.
Destiny's two debut music videos are on YouTube, iTunes, Spotify, SoundCloud, Vevo, and more. Destiny's music video, "I Feel Alive" has also been nominated for Music Video of the Year by the Hollywood Music Media Awards. Destiny will be walking the red carpet at the HMMA Awards on November 11, 2015.
Destiny has recently played at famous venues like, the House of Blues in Hollywood, the Viper Room on the Sunset Strip, the Canyon Club, Calamigos Ranch, and the Malibu Inn -among others. See Destiny "live" at one of her upcoming shows - St Andrews Hall, in Detroit, Michigan -October 27, 2015 at 9pm.
Stay connected with Destiny via her website: http://www.destinyofficial.com . Destiny also interacts with nearly 30,000 followers on her Instagram: DestinyOfficialMusic, which includes over 7,000 participants from over 100 countries entering on of her Remix Contests.
About Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes
Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes are the most widely distributed mixtapes in the world, with over 100 million downloads/plays generated by over 300 volumes officially hosted by major artists. Coast 2 Coast has a solid reach in the new music industry with a digital magazine, DJ coalition, industry tips blog, yearly convention, and more. Coast 2 Coast Mixtapes represents a unique opportunity for artists of all urban genres, from major to indie. For more information, visit http://www.coast2coastmixtapes.com .
